{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_ironsprings_ver01/data/sn84020064/00414217710/1927061901/0722.xml":{"full_text":"FOUR\nRAILWAY STOCK\nHOLDS INTEREST\nIN N. YJARKET\n(By the Associated Press)\nStock market averages:\nDate\u2014 20 Industrials 20 Rails\nSaturday 157.42 '144.38\nFriday 157.50 144.35\nWeek ago 157.86 144.21\nYear ago 139.51 117.81\nHigh, 1927 159.61 145.58\nLow, 1927 141.23 125.58\nTotal stock sales 1,071,700 shares.\nNEW YORK, June 18 (#).\u2014An under\ncurrent of strength ran through today\u2019s\nstock market despite rather heavy\nweek-end profit-taking and the un\ncovering of a few weak spots by bear\ntraders. Operators for the advance,\nencouraged by the belief that the stock\nmarket will draw a substantial part\nof $550,000,000 to be distributed in divi\ndend and interest payments next\nmonth, staged bullish demonstrations\nin a selected assortment of rails and\nspecialties, nearly a score of which\nwere elevated to record high levels.\nTrading was fairly heavy for a half\nholiday session, the day\u2019s sales aggre\ngating 1,071,000 shares.\nWith call money available in the\n\u201coutside market\u2019' as low as 3% per\ncent, speculators for the advance be\nlieve that they have nothing to fear\nfrom any immediate change in the\ncredit situation. The weekly federal\nSTOCK QUOTATIONS\nClosing Quotations Furnished by\nRICE COMPANY, Brokers,\n929 G Ave. Phone 119\nAtchison 180\nCanadian Pacific 178\nSt. Paul 16%\nSouthern Pacific 113%\nUnion Pacific 173%\nMissouri Pacific 57%\nRock Island 114\nNorthern Pacific 89\nBaltimore and Ohio 118%\nReading 118%\nNew York Central 152\nPennsylvania 63%\nKansas City Southern 61%\nU. S. Steel 121%\nBethlehem 49%\nVanadium 48\nAmerican Smelting 159%\nAnaconda\nMiami 14%\nInspiration 14%\nGranby 36%\nNevada Consolidated 14%\nCalumet and Arizona 65% 66\nKennecott 62%\nChile 34%\nGreene 45\nInternational Nickel 66%\nHowe 38%\nButte Superior 8%\nMagma 36%\nTexas Gulf Sulphur 64%\nRadio 51%\nAllied Chemical 140%\nAmerican 